@startuml
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
title Why a Golden Ticket works — the krbtgt key as root of trust

package "Domain Controller (KDC)" {
  [krbtgt account] as KRBTGT
  [krbtgt password hash\n= TGT signing/encryption key] as KEY
  [KDC: stateless,\nkeeps no list of issued TGTs] as KDC
}

[TGT\n(user, groups/SIDs,\nvalidity)] as TGT

KRBTGT --> KEY
KEY --> TGT : encrypts & signs
KDC ..> TGT : "is this TGT encrypted\nwith my krbtgt key?\n-> trust its contents"

note bottom of KDC
  The DC does not verify the user
  still exists or that the TGT was
  ever issued. Possession of the
  krbtgt hash = ability to mint a
  TGT for ANY identity, including
  fabricated ones.
end note
@enduml
